sql:
SELECT cohort_name
FROM cohorts
WHERE cohort_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT year
FROM academic_years
ORDER BY year;

SELECT cohort_name
FROM cohorts
ORDER BY cohort_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- A cohort refers to a group of students who share similar characteristics or experiences; 
- Average score and average percentile are used to evaluate the performance of each cohort; 
- Access count represents the number of times each cohort's performance data has been accessed; 
- Latest report details include the report date, user name, and email.
